HEADWORD: Crusher
<hw>Crush"er</hw> <pr>(-?r)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>One who, or that
which, crushes.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Crusher gauge</b></col>, <cd>an instrument for measuring
the explosive force of gunpowder, etc., by its effect in compressing a
piece of metal.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Crushing</ent>⟦br⟧
